Backup-SingleFile

This module can be used to copy one single file several times to the same 
destination-directory without overwriting the destination. (Keeps the history)
This is achived by postfixing the original filename with the date and a counter.

Useful for backing up important files from mobile devices (f.e. track-file from GPS-receivers) to your computers hard-drive.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Backup::SingleFile

You can also look for information at:

